@EndNode


@Node intro "What is VLTFONEBOOK?"

    Yet this another rexx vlt phone book.  Then you may ask there is already a
    VLTPHONEBOOK that comes with VLT package why we need another one.  Here is
    reasons that motivate me to write a new phone book.
    
    VLTPHONEBOOK is full feature phone book.  It can create phone book and 
    generate, delete, update entries.  But every entries of phone book is
    a seperate file.  When you try to dial a number, you first create a dial
    list (another file) then the dialer will dial one after another.  It also
    support precommand and postcommand.  One has to click 3 button to dial
    initial dialing process.  

    I personally has never used most of these features.  So I always though 
    I could simply VLTPHONEBOOK so that it only has one phone book file with 
    all entries in it.  It only need one click to dial a number.  It should
    runs faster and easy to customize the look.  It should try the number 
    until you get connected.  So VLTFONEBOOK was born.  

    Lot of credit should go to Willy for writting the original VLTPHONEBOOK.  
    Without such fine example, I might not be able to create VLTFONEBOOK at
    first place.  

    -- maji@carson.u.washington.edu

@EndNode

@Node instal "Put everything in place"

    Define VLTFONEBOOK: to point the location where all support file locates
    
        assign VLTFONEBOOK: Work:Comm/VLT/VLTFONEBOOK
    
    Copy all support file to it

        copy VLTFONEBOOK     VLTFONEBOOK:
        copy VLTDialer.rexx  VLTFONEBOOK:
        copy VLTFONEBOOK.vlt VLTFONEBOOK:
        copy test.vlt        VLTFONEBOOK:
        copy vlt.rexx        VLTFONEBOOK:

    You are all set!

@EndNode

@Node custom "Change the look of phone pannel"

1) Change the name field inside phone book
    .count how many charactors for the name field
    .change "namesize =" number inside .vlt

2) Change maximum number of entries on the pannel
    .change "MaxFE =" number inside .vlt

3) For modem that does not support hardware handshake
   replace hangupscript with following:

hangupscript = "$vltphone_wait: on (OK) continue; send (+++); delay 2; "        
hangupscript = hangupscript || "send (ATH*R); delay 15; on (OK) (); send (*R*R)"    

@EndNode

@Node undertm "Run VLTFONEBOOK under ToolManager"

    Create a exec object of ToolManager with following entries:
    
    Object Name: VLT                    Current Directory: VLTFoneBook:
    Exec Type  : Arexx                  Path             :
    Command    : VLTFoneBook:vlt.rexx   Output File      :
    Hot Key    : F1                     Public Screen    : VLT
    Stack      : 4096                   
    Priority   : 0                      [ ] Arguments
    Delay      : 0                      [v] To Front

    Then press F1 see the action!

@EndNode

@Node bug "Something not quite right yet"

    The only way to break the dial process is when you see the dial number
    quickly click on VLT screen and if OK is the response, then script exit

    report other bugs to:
        maji@carson.u.washington.edu

@EndNode

